Message.MsgText: soapcontainer.service=WSWS6003I: The SOAP Container Service is initialized.
Message.Explanation: This informational message indicates the program status.

Message.MsgText: no.system.application=WSWS6001E: Received request {0} for unregistered system service endpoint {1}.
Message.Explanation: A request was received for a system application that is not installed and deployed.
Message.UserResponse: Verify the system endpoint name and check for errors during server startup.

Message.MsgText: no.system.router=WSWS6002E: No system endpoint router is defined for request {0}.
Message.Explanation: No router is defined for the incoming request.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that valid system service endpoints are defined with valid system endpoint configuration files.

Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .
